# -*- mode: org -*-
#+TITLE: formats: binhextools build wiring + endianness + orphaned trees
#+DATE: 2026-06-20

* TODO [#A] formats: build wiring, byte-order, and dead/orphaned sources  :formats:build:memory:endianness:
  Full-tree review 2026-06-20 (gcc/g++ 14, strict flags). Macintosh file-format
  tools (BinHex, MacBinary, single/double fork). The binhexlib stream core is
  clean and the BinHex 6-bit alphabet matches the spec; the *tools* are in poor
  shape. See [[build-system]].

** Build-blockers

*** [critical] binhextools — libbinhexlib.a + SevenStream.hh/RunLengthStream.hh not found
One root cause: =binhexlib= is never installed into =$(PREFIX)=.
=binhextools/sources/Makefile= references =-I$(PREFIX)/lib/binhexlib/interfaces=
and =$(PREFIX)/lib/binhexlib/libraries/libbinhexlib.a=, but =make all= from the
top never *installs* binhexlib first (the project loop only runs each module's
=all=). The headers live in =binhexlib/interfaces/= and the =.a= stays in
=binhexlib/sources/=.
Fix (preferred): repoint binhextools' INCLUDES/LIBS at the in-tree sibling
(=-I../../binhexlib/interfaces= and =../../binhexlib/sources/libbinhexlib.a=) so
it no longer depends on an install step. Alternative: drive the top build with
=make install= (MODULES lists binhexlib before binhextools).

*** [critical] single_to_double/s2d.c:542,543 — strncpy truncation (-Werror=stringop-truncation)
=fdType=/=fdCreator= are =OSType= = =char[4]= fixed tags (not C strings), so no
NUL is wanted, but gcc14 flags the call regardless.
Fix: =memcpy(ffork.finfo.fdType,"TEXT",4);= (and ="UNIX"=).

*** [critical] macbinary/sources/mb.c:652 — 'dontoverride' set but not used
Assigned =TRUE= and never read (the comment even says "useless").
Fix: delete the declaration/assignment.

** Orphaned / unbuildable trees (excluded from MODULES, do not add as-is)

*** [high] formats/macbinary_to_triple/mb2t.c — dead, won't compile on gcc14
Not in the top Makefile MODULES. K&R definitions, =//= comments under strict
C99-pedantic, =close()= on =FILE*= (should be =fclose=, lines 461/464/482/503/517/525),
undeclared =nil=/=boolean=/=int32=/=int16=, =sprintf= into a 32-byte buffer (:117).
Superseded by =macbinary/sources/mb.c=. Confirm retired; delete or document.

*** [high] single_to_double/encours/ — abandoned NeXTSTEP Objective-C WIP
=#import <objc/Object.h>=, =<streams/streams.h>=, =NXStream=, =#include
<PJBTypes.h> // OBSOLETE=; none exist on Linux. ASSegment.m also has real bugs:
=+new:stream:= references the instance ivar =lastError= from a class method (:60),
and =-changeStream:= assigns =myStream=s= where =s= is undefined (:89).
Treat =encours/= as excluded source.

** Latent bugs

*** [critical] binhextools/sources/bh.c:296 — entire encode/decode logic is dead code
=main= parses options, echoes them, then =return(0);= at :296. Everything after
(create/extract at 298-331) is unreachable, and the bodies below are empty stubs.
=bh=/=bhencode=/=bhdecode= do nothing but echo arguments.
Fix: remove the debug block and premature return; implement the body.

*** [high] s2d.c:149,166 (and mb2t.c:133,149) — magic compared without byte-swap
=header.magic= is read raw and compared to =AppleSD_Single_Magic= (0x00051600),
but AppleSingle/Double store fields *big-endian*; on little-endian Linux genuine
files fail the test and s2d silently exits 0. All multi-byte on-disk fields
(=entryCount=, =entry.offset/length=, =fdFlags=) have the same defect.
Fix: byte-swap every on-disk field (=be32toh=/=htobe32=, or assemble from bytes
like mb.c's =toCARD32=).

*** [high] s2d.c:248 — unvalidated entry.offset/length drives fseek/fread
=AppleSD_CopyData=/=GetType= seek to =entry.offset= and copy =entry.length= bytes
straight from header values, no bounds check vs file size; =entry.length= is
signed so a negative value drives a near-infinite copy.
Fix: validate =offset>=0=, =length>=0=, =offset+length<=filesize=.

*** [medium] binhexlib/RunLengthStream.cc:107 — run-length count underflow
After marker =0x90=, =length= is =CARD8=; a stream =0x90 0x01= makes
=DECR(length,2)= = 255, emitting the previous byte 255 times.
Fix: reject =length<2= after a marker as corrupt.

*** [medium] macbinary/mb.c:392 — MacBinary_Skip checks wrong variable
After reading =padding= bytes it tests =if(count!=size)= but =size= is 0 here;
a short read of the padding is not detected. Fix: compare against =padding=.

*** [medium] mb.c:587 — type-punned *(CARD32*)&info->type (aliasing + endian display)
Strict-aliasing violation and prints the 4-byte tag in host byte order.
Fix: print the four bytes individually or assemble big-endian.

*** [medium] mb.c:494 / s2d.c basename/makeresourcefilename — unbounded strcpy/strcat
=forkopen= does =strcpy(name,fname);strcat(name,extension)= into =CHAR name[1024]=
with no guard; =makeresourcefilename=/=basename= copy into fixed buffers unbounded.
Long paths overflow. Fix: bounded copies / =snprintf=.

*** [low] mb.c:310 — strcpy of a possibly-not-NUL-terminated 63-byte Mac name
=strcpy(finfo->name,header->name)= when =nameLength==63= can over-read.
Fix: bound by =nameLength= and NUL-terminate. Also s2d.c:406 =basename= shadows
POSIX =basename(3)=; rename to =s2d_basename=.

** Health
Build is broken by four hard stops (binhexlib wiring, s2d strncpy, mb.c unused);
two source trees are orphaned/unbuildable. Once those are fixed, =bh.c= is a
non-functional stub and =s2d.c=/=mb2t.c= mishandle endianness and trust on-disk
sizes — those are the priority for correctness.
